Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Fill a large #saucepan{} with the boiling water and put on high heat. Bring back to the boil.

Add @salt{1/2%tsp} and the @linguine{180%g}. Cook for ~{12%minutes}.

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. Add the @chicken breast{260%g}(diced) to the pan and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, fry until golden on the outside, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} to the chicken.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden all over, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the bottom 2cm off the @asparagus{100%g} and discard. Cut the asparagus widthways into 3cm long pieces.

Once the mushrooms and bacon are golden, stir in the garlic for ~{30%seconds}. When the pasta has 3 mins left, add the asparagus to the water. Once the pasta and asparagus are cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Save @reserved pasta water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Once the asparagus and pasta are drained, stir in the saved pasta water, the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the mushrooms.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the drained pasta and asparagus, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} into the sauce and gently toss to coat.

> TIP: Add another splash of pasta water if the sauce is still a bit thick.

Season to taste with a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Share between your bowls and dig in. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 2: If you've opted to add chicken breast to your meal, then before adding the bacon and mushrooms to your pan, add the chicken to the pan and season with salt and pepper, fry until golden on the outside, 3-4 mins. Add the mushrooms and bacon to the pan and continue with the rest of the recipe. - Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.